I think that the easiest way to determine whether the host supports smtp
or not is to just try to open the connection. If it gets refused, they
don't ... the only extra win you could get is things like sendmail will
call this a temporary error and will try again until the message times
out (in case the server is just down temporarily) -- if it looked at the
WKS record, it might be able to send an error quicker, but it sounds
pretty useless ... what I'd much rather see is a way for identifying
which hosts do specific services ... rather than asking "does host X
do service Y?" I'd like to see "Which hosts in domain Z do service Y?"

This would be really useful for local services ... the information
returned should be a port number to contact and a list of hosts.

/jordan

